title: Paraguayan Tennis Players Advance in International Tournament in Chile - Archyworldys
text:
Kindness Asuncion, IP Agency.- Several compatriots remain stuck in the different categories of the tournament at the Stade Francais in Santiago, Chile, validated by the ITF at 18 years of age and by COSAT in the 16 and 14 categories.
The main figure is undoubtedly Victoria López Ocampos, who, in the 18-player group, is in the singles quarterfinals and with her sister Ana in the doubles semi-finals.
In the round of 16, Victoria López defeated local Samantha Álvarez 6-2, 6-3 and will face France’s Alice Chatiliez in the quarterfinals this Thursday for a spot in the semifinals. Sisters Ana and Victoria advanced to the semifinals of the ITF 18 after beating Peruvians Renata Rossell and Mia Zorrilla 6-1, 7-5.
In the COSAT category, Delfina Pereira defeated Argentina’s Ana Clara Bonavita 6-3 6-3 and will then face Brazil’s Martina Toniasso Mattos. Facundo Moreira, also still in the running, will face Chile’s Agustín Jarabran in the quarterfinals. Likewise, in the doubles Facundo and Tomás Moreira, as well as Delfina Pereira together with Peru’s Triana Tocon García.
On the other hand, the national team’s number 1 tennis player, Adolfo Daniel Vallejo Álvarez, eliminated prematurely in his first appearances in singles and doubles in Manacor, continues to train at the Rafa Nadal Open venue until tomorrow, Friday, when he will travel to Cassis, the spa town on the French blue coast where he will play another Challenger 75, for which he will have to play the qualifications.La Tribuna.
